              <article id="help-answers-4" class="well">
                <h3>How do I integrate my repository with Wisply?</h3>
                <br />
                In case you want to integrate your repository with Wisply, you can <a href="/contact">contact us</a>. We will make sure that Wisply will gather metadata data from it.
              </article>
              <article id="help-answers-5" class="well">
                <h3>How can I remove a resource from Wisply?</h3>
                <br />
                We apologize for this inconvenience. Wispy is collecting in an automate way data from open repositories.
                <br />
                We have a take down policy regarding the data, which you can read it <a href="/take-down-policy">here</a>.
                <br />
                In case you consider that a resource should not appear on Wisply, please <a href="/contact">contact us</a> and we will remove it.
              </article>
              <article id="help-answers-6" class="well">
                <h3>The content for some resources is not visible. Why?</h3>
                <br />
                Wisply is collecting metadata about all the resources from a repository. The metadata may include the date, the creators, the formats and many other details. As you see, Wisply does not get the actual files.
                <br /><br />
                For some resources, Wisply has a mechanism which collects the previous images. This mechanism helps the users to get an idea about the resource.
                <br /><br />
                <b>Why not for all?</b>
                <br />
                There are two reasons:
                <br />
                <ul>
                  <li> The content can't be displayed in the browser</li>
                  <li> The resource is not public, thus is not visible to Wisply</li>
                </ul>
              </article>
